HEADWORD: Double-ripper
<hw>Dou"ble-rip"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of
coasting sled, made of two sleds fastened together with a board, one
before the other.</def> <mark>[Local, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

